    <li>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Chlorination is the process of adding chlorine to drinking water to kill parasites, bacteria, and viruses. Different processes can be used to achieve safe levels of chlorine in drinking water.</li>
<li >&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Raw water is obtained from protected source  (i.e.) bore wall.</li>
<li>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;Dosing sodium hypo chlorite solution ( chlorine) is done on the pipeline to the protected raw water tank for initial  disinfection to avoid microbiological contamination.</li>
<li>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;In the raw water tank, minimum contact time is made with chlorine and sediment of suspended particles. Feeding chlorine in the pipeline from bore well to raw water tank is made to reduce this lead time, as the chlorine mixes well inside the pipeline due to the flow force.</li>

